data.name: BBQ Glazed Salmon with Asparagus and Sweet Potato Mash
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously grilled salmon with a sweet BBQ glaze paired with vibrant asparagus and creamy sweet potato mash.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or oven to medium-high heat.
Season the salmon fillets with salt and pepper. Brush BBQ sauce generously over the top.
Place the salmon on the grill or a baking sheet (if using the oven) and cook for about 6-8 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.
While the salmon is cooking, peel and chop the sweet potatoes. Boil them in a pot of salted water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain the sweet potatoes, then mash them with a bit of olive oil, salt, and pepper until creamy.
In the last 5 minutes of cooking the salmon, toss the asparagus with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Grill or roast them until tender, about 5 minutes.
Serve the BBQ glazed salmon alongside the sweet potato mash and asparagus.
data.detailedName: BBQ Glazed Salmon with Asparagus and Sweet Potato Mash
